      <Docs>
        <summary>Occurs when the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Markup.Localizer.BamlLocalizer" /> encounters abnormal conditions.</summary>
        <remarks>
          <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 Under normal circumstances, <xref:System.Windows.Markup.Localizer.BamlLocalizer> ignores errors and continues localizing the source BAML input. As a result, the output BAML is partially localized. By listening for errors this event can be used to stop the <xref:System.Windows.Markup.Localizer.BamlLocalizer> and stop processing a source BAML file.  
  
 The most common user case where <xref:System.Windows.Markup.Localizer.BamlLocalizer.ErrorNotify> might be raised is as a result of an <xref:System.Windows.Markup.Localizer.BamlLocalizer.UpdateBaml%2A> call where the update contained errors. For example, the event is raised if an attempted update set a duplicate key, or if the original and update did not have UID values that align.  
  
 ]]></format>
        </remarks>
      </Docs>
